article.headline: Western Kentucky 87, Austin Peay 80
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Winchester scored 29 points, 21 coming from 3-point range, to lead Western Kentucky to an 87-80 victory over Austin Peay on Tuesday night. The Hilltoppers (9-1) took control of a close game in the final six minutes after regaining the lead 74-73 on a free throw by Courtney Lee, who finished with 15 points. Western Kentucky hit 10 of 14 free throws in the final 6:15 to seal the game. Elgrace Wilborn had 11 points and 13 rebounds for Western Kentucky, while Danny Rumph added 11 points. Maurice Hampton scored 20 points to lead the Governors (2-8), including four 3-pointers. Anthony Davis had 18 points and 10 rebounds for Austin Peay, and Zac Schlader scored 17 and William Durden 11. Austin Peay led most of the first half, taking a 27-17 lead with 8:46 left on a tip-in by Hampton. The Governors shot 60 percent in the first half and took a 46-39 lead to halftime after leading by as many as 13. The Governors cooled off in the second half while Western Kentucky remained consistent from the field. Both teams shot 51.7 percent for the game. The Hilltoppers chipped away at the lead and went ahead 51-50 with 16:34 to play on a 3-pointer by Winchester, who was 7 of 9 from long range in the game. Austin Peay took its final lead at 71-70 with seven minutes left on a free throw by Durden. A dunk by Wilborn with 3:45 to play gave Western Kentucky an 80-73 lead, and the Hilltoppers made it stand in the final minutes by hitting their free throws. Western Kentucky was 17 of 24 from the free throw line for the game, with Austin Peay 11 of 15.
